The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 October is 3,571 (413.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 September, there were 162 new confirmed cases (18.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 September, there were 121 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 34% (41 extra cases).
